🌐 DORA Process (DHCP ka funda)

⚡ Full form → Discover – Offer – Request – Acknowledge
👉 Ye ek 4 step process hai jo hota hai jab koi device (PC, mobile, laptop, router) network pe aata hai aur IP address khud se maangta hai DHCP server se.

🔹 Step 1: Discover (D)

        Jab ek new device network pe connect hota hai (jaise Wi-Fi join karta hai), uske paas abhi koi IP address nahi hota.
        
        Wo ek broadcast message bhejta hai → "Koi DHCP server hai kya? Mujhe ek IP chahiye!"

👉 Real Life Example (Hindi):
        Soch tu ek hotel me aaya hai bina room book kiye. Tu reception pe jaake bolta hai:
        "Hello! Koi room khaali hai kya? Mujhe ek room chahiye."

🔹 Step 2: Offer (O)

        Jo DHCP Server hota hai wo sunta hai aur reply karta hai → "Haan mere paas IP address hai. Tu 192.168.1.10 use kar sakta hai. Saath me subnet mask, gateway, DNS bhi de raha hu."
        
        Ye ek offer hoti hai, matlab ek suggestion.

👉 Hotel Example:
        Receptionist bolta hai:
        "Yes, ek room khaali hai. Tu Room No. 101 le sakta hai."

🔹 Step 3: Request (R)

        Ab client (device) confirm karta hai aur bolta hai → "Ok mujhe ye 192.168.1.10 wali IP chahiye. Please ye reserve kar do sirf mere liye."
        
        Ye ek request hoti hai.

👉 Hotel Example:
        Tu receptionist ko bolta hai:
        "Ok mujhe Room No. 101 pasand hai. Main wahi lunga. Dusre guest ko mat dena."

🔹 Step 4: Acknowledge (A)

        Ab DHCP Server officially confirm karta hai aur bolta hai → "Theek hai, ab se 192.168.1.10 teri IP hai. Ab isse use kar."
        
        Iske saath hi client ko Subnet Mask, Default Gateway, DNS Server ka data bhi milta hai.

👉 Hotel Example:
        Receptionist bolta hai:
        "Theek hai sir. Room No. 101 ab officially aapka hai. Ye keys le lijiye."

✅ Final Result

      Device ke paas proper IP configuration aa jata hai:
      
      IP Address
      
      Subnet Mask
      
      Default Gateway
      
      DNS Server

Ab wo network pe dusre devices aur Internet ke sath baat kar sakta hai.

🔑 Shortcut Formula (yaad rakhne ka easy way)

        D → Discover = "Koi hai mujhe IP dene wala?"
        
        O → Offer = "Haan, ye IP le sakta hai."
        
        R → Request = "Mujhe ye IP chahiye."
        
        A → Acknowledge = "Ok, ye IP ab teri hai."

👉 Matlab DORA = ek hotel me room allotment jaisa hai.

      IP = Room Number
      
      DHCP Server = Receptionist
      
      Client = Guest (Tu)
